gov.va.vinci.leo.listener

Class BaseCsvListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.uima.aae.client.UimaAsBaseCallbackListener
      • gov.va.vinci.leo.listener.BaseListener
        • gov.va.vinci.leo.listener.BaseCsvListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.uima.aae.client.UimaASStatusCallbackListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleCsvListener

    public abstract class BaseCsvListener
extends BaseListener
    Base gov.va.vinci.leo.listener for creating CSV output. Implementing classes need to implement getHeaders() and getRows().

    If not overridden in the constructors, the default separator is a comma (,), the default quote character is a quote("), the default escape character is a backslash (\), and the default line ending is a newline (\n)

      • writeHeaders

        public void writeHeaders()
                  throws IOException
        Write out headers to the writerBuilder for this gov.va.vinci.leo.listener. The idea being this might be called once before the process is started to write out column headers to the csv file.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the headers cannot be written.
